Event.0: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi launches "Modicare", free heathcare for 500 million, world's biggest healthcare program
Event.1: Actress Lisa Linde (39) divorces "Xmen" actor James Marsden (38) due to irreconcilable differences after 11 years of marriage
Event.2: American folk musician Etta Baker, who influenced the folk music revival of the 1950s and '60s with her blend of Piedmont blues and bluegrass, died at age 93.
Event.3: American choreographer and director Bob Fosse—who revolutionized musicals with his distinct style of dance, including his frequent use of props, signature moves, and provocative steps—died in Washington, D.C.
Event.4: ABC's 1st color TV series - The Jetsons by Hanna-Barbera first broadcast
Event.5: President Dwight D. Eisenhower orders US troops to support integration of nine black students at Little Rock Central High School in Arkansas
Event.6: "That'll Be Day" by Buddy Holly & Crickets reaches #1
Event.7:

Event.8: American singer, songwriter, and bandleader Bruce Springsteen, who became the archetypal rock performer of the 1970s and '80s, was born.

Julio Iglesias
Spanish singer and songwriter
was born
Event.10: Sigmund Freud, the founder of modern psychoanalysis, died in London.
Event.11: Gangster Sam Giancana (25) weds Angeline De Tolve

Event.14: Film producer Samuel Goldwyn (33) divorces first wife Blanche Lasky after 5 years of marriage
Event.15: Nintendo Koppai (Later Nintendo Company, Limited) founded by Fusajiro Yamauchi to produce and market the playing card game Hanafuda
Event.16: American Herman Hollerith patents his mechanical tabulating machine, the beginning of data processing
Event.17: A small group of Puerto Rican radicals committed to independence attempted an uprising, El Grito de Lares; the revolt was crushed by the Spanish.
Event.18: Russian novelist and author of "War and Peace" Leo Tolstoy (34) marries Sophia Andreevna Behrs (18) daughter of a physician
Event.19: Otto von Bismarck was appointed prime minister of Prussia by William I.
Event.20:
Neptune observed
This day in 1846, astronomer Johann Gottfried Galle became the first person ever to observe the planet Neptune, the existence of which had been mathematically predicted by Urbain-Jean-Joseph Le Verrier and John Couch Adams.
Event.21: 1st baseball team, NY Knickerbockers organize, adopt rule code
Event.22: Fall of Tripolitsa, Greek forces massacre 30,000 Turks during Greek War of Independence
Event.23: Lewis and Clark arrived in St. Louis, Missouri, at the end of their daring expedition to the Pacific Northwest.
Event.24: During the American Revolution, in the midst of a naval engagement between the warships Bonhomme Richard and Serapis off the east coast of England, American commander John Paul Jones answered a call to surrender from his English counterpart with the famous quotation, “I have not yet begun to fight!”
Event.25: Princess Maria of Orange-Nassau marries Mauritius earl of Simmeren
Event.26: Concordat of Worms agreed between Pope Calixtus II and Holy Roman Emperor Henry V
